1058
1059const std::array<std::pair<uint16_t, UChar>, 7724>& jis0208()
1060{
1061 // Allocate this at runtime because building it at compile time would make the binary much larger and this is often not used.
1062 static std::array<std::pair<uint16_t, UChar>, 7724>* array;
1063 static std::once_flag flag;
1064 std::call_once(flag, [] {
1065 array = new std::array<std::pair<uint16_t, UChar>, 7724>;
1066 size_t arrayIndex = 0;
1067
1068 UErrorCode error = U_ZERO_ERROR;
1069 auto icuConverter = ICUConverterPtr { ucnv_open("EUC-JP", &error) };
1070 ASSERT(!error);
1071
1072 constexpr size_t range = 94;
1073 uint8_t icuInput[2];
1074 UChar icuOutput;
1075 for (size_t i = 0; i < range; i++) {
1076 for (size_t j = 0; j < range; j++) {
1077 icuInput[0] = 0xA1 + i;
1078 icuInput[1] = 0xA1 + j;
1079
1080 UChar* output = &icuOutput;
1081 const char* input = reinterpret_cast<const char*>(icuInput);
1082 ucnv_toUnicode(icuConverter.get(), &output, output + 1, &input, input + sizeof(icuInput), nullptr, true, &error);
1083 ASSERT(!error);
1084 if (icuOutput != 0xFFFD) {
1085 uint16_t pointer = i * range + j;
1086 (*array)[arrayIndex++] = { pointer, icuOutput };
1087 }
1088 }
1089 }
1090
1091 for (auto& extra : jis0208Extras)
1092 (*array)[arrayIndex++] = extra;
1093 RELEASE_ASSERT_WITH_SECURITY_IMPLICATION(arrayIndex == 7724);
1094 ASSERT(*array == jis0208Reference);
1095 });
1096 return *array;
1097}

1863
1864const std::array<std::pair<uint16_t, UChar>, 6067>& jis0212()
1865{
1866 // Allocate this at runtime because building it at compile time would make the binary much larger and this is often not used.
1867 static std::array<std::pair<uint16_t, UChar>, 6067>* array;
1868 static std::once_flag flag;
1869 std::call_once(flag, [] {
1870 array = new std::array<std::pair<uint16_t, UChar>, 6067>();
1871 size_t arrayIndex = 0;
1872
1873 UErrorCode error = U_ZERO_ERROR;
1874 auto icuConverter = ICUConverterPtr { ucnv_open("EUC-JP", &error) };
1875 ASSERT(!error);
1876
1877 constexpr size_t range = 94;
1878 uint8_t icuInput[3];
1879 UChar icuOutput;
1880 for (size_t i = 0; i < range; i++) {
1881 for (size_t j = 0; j < range; j++) {
1882 icuInput[0] = 0x8F;
1883 icuInput[1] = 0xA1 + i;
1884 icuInput[2] = 0xA1 + j;
1885
1886 UChar* output = &icuOutput;
1887 const char* input = reinterpret_cast<const char*>(icuInput);
1888 ucnv_toUnicode(icuConverter.get(), &output, output + 1, &input, input + sizeof(icuInput), nullptr, true, &error);
1889 ASSERT(!error);
1890 if (icuOutput != 0xFFFD) {
1891 uint16_t pointer = i * range + j;
1892 // ICU has some pointers above 7708 that are not in the encoding standard.
1893 if (pointer < 7708)
1894 (*array)[arrayIndex++] = { pointer, icuOutput };
1895 }
1896 }
1897 }
1898
1899 RELEASE_ASSERT_WITH_SECURITY_IMPLICATION(arrayIndex == 6067);
1900 ASSERT(*array == jis0212Reference);
1901 });
1902 return *array;
1903}

7066
7067const std::array<std::pair<uint16_t, UChar>, 17048>& eucKR()
7068{
7069 // Allocate this at runtime because building it at compile time would make the binary much larger and this is often not used.
7070 static std::array<std::pair<uint16_t, UChar>, 17048>* array;
7071 static std::once_flag flag;
7072 std::call_once(flag, [] {
7073 array = new std::array<std::pair<uint16_t, UChar>, 17048>;
7074 UErrorCode error = U_ZERO_ERROR;
7075 auto icuConverter = ICUConverterPtr { ucnv_open("windows-949", &error) };
7076 ASSERT(U_SUCCESS(error));
7077 auto getPair = [icuConverter = WTFMove(icuConverter)] (uint16_t pointer) -> std::optional<std::pair<uint16_t, UChar>> {
7078 std::array<uint8_t, 2> icuInput { static_cast<uint8_t>(pointer / 190u + 0x81), static_cast<uint8_t>(pointer % 190u + 0x41) };
7079 const char* input = reinterpret_cast<const char*>(icuInput.data());
7080 UChar icuOutput[2];
7081 UChar* output = icuOutput;
7082 UErrorCode error = U_ZERO_ERROR;
7083 ucnv_toUnicode(icuConverter.get(), &output, output + 2, &input, input + sizeof(icuInput), nullptr, true, &error);
7084 if (icuOutput[0] == 0xFFFD)
7085 return std::nullopt;
7086 return {{ pointer, icuOutput[0] }};
7087 };
7088 size_t arrayIndex = 0;
7089 for (uint16_t pointer = 0; pointer < 13776; pointer++) {
7090 if (auto pair = getPair(pointer))
7091 (*array)[arrayIndex++] = WTFMove(*pair);
7092 }
7093 for (uint16_t pointer = 13870; pointer < 23750; pointer++) {
7094 if (auto pair = getPair(pointer))
7095 (*array)[arrayIndex++] = WTFMove(*pair);
7096 }
7097 RELEASE_ASSERT_WITH_SECURITY_IMPLICATION(arrayIndex == 17048);
7098 ASSERT(*array == eucKRDecodingIndexReference);
7099 });
7100 return *array;
7101}

8605
8606const std::array<UChar, 23940>& gb18030()
8607{
8608 // Allocate this at runtime because building it at compile time would make the binary much larger and this is often not used.
8609 static std::array<UChar, 23940>* array;
8610 static std::once_flag flag;
8611 std::call_once(flag, [] {
8612 array = new std::array<UChar, 23940>;
8613 UErrorCode error = U_ZERO_ERROR;
8614 auto icuConverter = ICUConverterPtr { ucnv_open("gb18030", &error) };
8615 for (size_t pointer = 0; pointer < 23940; pointer++) {
8616 uint8_t icuInput[2];
8617 icuInput[0] = pointer / 190 + 0x81;
8618 icuInput[1] = pointer % 190;
8619 icuInput[1] += (icuInput[1] < 0x3F) ? 0x40 : 0x41;
8620 UChar icuOutput { 0 };
8621 UChar* output = &icuOutput;
8622 const char* input = reinterpret_cast<const char*>(icuInput);
8623 ucnv_toUnicode(icuConverter.get(), &output, output + 1, &input, input + sizeof(icuInput), nullptr, true, &error);
8624 ASSERT(!error);
8625 ASSERT(icuOutput != 0xFFFD);
8626 (*array)[pointer] = icuOutput;
8627 }
8628
8629 // This is a difference between ICU and the encoding specification.
8630 ASSERT((*array)[6555] == 0xe5e5);
8631 (*array)[6555] = 0x3000;
8632
8633 ASSERT(*array == gb18030Reference);
8634 });
8635 return *array;
8636}
